Package io.github.gfrmoretti

Class AnMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.gfrmoretti.AnMap
  • public class AnMap
extends Object
    AnMap (Annotation Mapper)

    This class represents the lib itself, because all map actions must be trigger here. This class has all map actions possibles for user to use.

        Map any class to any target since the field can be mapped.
        Type Parameters:
        Source - type of the source data class.
        Target - type of the target to map and return.
        Parameters:
        source - instance of the class with the data source to be transfer to target class.
        targetClass - a target Class that you want to receive the source data.
        Returns:

      • mapReference

        public static <Source,​Target> void mapReference​(@Nullable
                                                      Source source,
                                                      @Nullable
                                                      Target target)
        Map by reference any class to any target since the field can be mapped. This method, update the non-null fields in reference target, using this, the AnMap do not need to create a target instance, it already received the instance and put the non-null fields from source in the target instance.
        Type Parameters:
        Source - type of the source data class.
        Target - type of the target to map.
        Parameters:
        source - instance of the class with the data source to be transfer to target instance.
        target - a target instance that you want to receive the source data.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if AnMap can not map the class.

      • mapReference

        public static <Source,​Target> void mapReference​(@Nullable
                                                      Source source,
                                                      @Nullable
                                                      Target target,
                                                      @NotNull
                                                      @NotNull AnnotationSide side)
        Map by reference any class to any target since the field can be mapped. This method, update the non-null fields in reference target, using this, the AnMap do not need to create a target instance, it already received the instance and put the non-null fields from source in the target instance. You can specify which side (Source or Target) the AnMap must consider to process the annotations.
        Type Parameters:
        Source - type of the source data class.
        Target - type of the target to map.
        Parameters:
        source - instance of the class with the data source to be transfer to target instance.
        target - a target instance that you want to receive the source data.
        side - the AnnotationSide to process the annotations.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if AnMap can not map the class.

      • mapCustom

        public static <Source,​Target> Optional<Target> mapCustom​(@Nullable
                                                               Source source,
                                                               @Nullable
                                                               @Nullable CustomMapper<Source,​Target> customMapper)
        This method make a custom map using the interface CustomMapper. When you want to full personalize the mapper and still using the library, you have this method to do that.
        Type Parameters:
        Source - type of the source data class.
        Target - type of the target to map and return.
        Parameters:
        source - instance of the class with the data source to be transfer to target instance.
        customMapper - an instance of the custom mapper interface.
        Returns:
        An Optional with the instance of the Target class with the data get from the source, or an empty optional if something fail to map.
